3. Derivation I: \mathbf{m = 1.878} as a Static Equilibrium (The \mathbf{\Lambda_\kappa} Link)
The exponent \mathbf{m} is derived from the static, weak-field equilibrium limit (\dot{\kappa}_{\mu\nu} \approx 0), where the system's geometry is stabilized by the Curvature Stiffness, \mathbf{\Lambda_\kappa}.

