4. Derivation II: \mathbf{\Gamma_\kappa} and the Dynamic Threshold
The universal value \mathbf{m = 1.878} is only observed in systems above a critical stellar mass (M_{\text{crit}} \approx 5 \times 10^9 M_{\odot}). 
This threshold is governed by the Dissipative Resistance (\mathbf{\Gamma_\kappa}), which is also responsible for the dynamic failure at the Critical Kinematic Velocity (\mathbf{v_c \approx 100 \text{ km s}^{-1}}).

4.1. The Dynamic Phase Transition
The value \mathbf{v_c} represents a geometric phase transition where the system's kinetic energy flux causes the local field stability (\mathbf{p_v}) to collapse, defined by the \mathbf{\Gamma_\kappa} term in the MEFE.
